report_ccopt_clock_tree_drv(25.10)          report_ccopt_clock_tree_drv(25.10)

Name
       report_ccopt_clock_tree_drv  -  This  command  is used to report design
       rule violations (DRVs) in the clock network

Syntax
       report_ccopt_clock_tree_drv

       [-help]

       [-clock_trees {<list_of_clock_trees>}]

       [-delay_corners <list_of_delay_corner_names>]

       [-drv_types {transition max_cap max_source_to_sink_net_length}]

       [-early]

       [-exclude_violation_types {dont_touch_nets pre_routed_nets}]

       [-file file_name]

       [-late]

       [-num_nets num | all]

       [-views {<list_of_views>}]

       This command is used to report design rule  violations  (DRVs)  in  the
       clock network.

       The report consists of three sections:

              * Constraint  summary:  Lists all the implicit and explicit tar-
                gets that CTS is targetting, along with which corners are  be-
                ing constrained.

              * Violation  summary:  Counts nets in the DAG with what types of
                violations exist.

              * Top N detailed net violation listing: Outputs a detailed  list
                of nets that have violations.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each report_ccopt_clock_tree_drv  parameter. For a
              detailed description of the command and all of  its  parameters,
              use the man command:

               man report_ccopt_clock_tree_drv

       -clock_trees {<list_of_clock_trees>}
              Restricts  the  report to the specified clock trees. By default,
              it reports DRVs for all clock trees.

       -delay_corners <list_of_delay_corner_names>
              Filters the report for a specific constrained delay  corner.  By
              default, it reports for all delay corners.

       -drv_types {transition max_cap max_source_to_sink_net_length}
              Filters  to  choose  the types of violation to report on. By de-
              fault, all types of violations are reported.

       -early Reports only the early half of the delay corners.

       -exclude_violation_types {dont_touch_nets pre_routed_nets}
              Specifies certain nets to be excluded if they are  known  to  be
              not  fixable.  By default, all nets are included. You can choose
              to exclude dont_touch nets and pre-routed nets.

       -file file_name
              Saves a copy of the contents of the report to the specified file
              name.

              Default: {}

       -late  Reports only the late half of the delay corners.

       -num_nets num | all
              Specifies the number of nets for which the violations should  be
              reported.  You can specify a number or specify all to report for
              all nets. By default, violations are rpeorted for 10 nets.

       -views {<list_of_views>}
              Restricts the report to the delay corners  associated  with  the
              specified views.

Example
       Use  the following command to report the violations for all nets in the
       specified report file:

       report_ccopt_clock_tree_drv -num_nets all -out_file report_file1

       For sample report, see Clock Tree Network DRV Reporting.

